doc.after: The close geographic and cultural ties between the Riverina and northern Victoria combined with continuing frustration with inter colonial tariffs made the Riverina a fertile area for ideas for uniting the various colonies in an Australian federation This would see the southern Riverina in particular take a leading role in bringing about federation
